    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-09-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-09-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="16"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d16">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Minister <persName type="to">Furniss</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-09-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 22, 1906</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 42.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your No. 90,
                    of the 24th ultimo, and your No. 93, of the 1st instant, regarding the new
                    tariff law of Haiti.</p>
                <p>The department approves your suggestion to the Haitian Government that goods on
                    ships bound to Haiti at the date of promulgation of the law should be allowed to
                    enter at the old rates.</p>
                <p>In your discretion you may use your personal offices in behalf of the American
                    protestants. The department does not, however, see that they have any legal
                    claim against the Haitian Government.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
